cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.MM

The paper deals with a communication system and proposes a deep learning-based approach for channel prediction. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also extensively uses neural networks, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely category as well. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel approach to channel prediction, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also uses AI techniques, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with Massive MIMO channel models and measurements, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
